'''Hensleigh Carthew Marryat "Car" Norris''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|QSO}} (12 March 1893 &ndash; 3 September 1980) was a New Zealand lawyer, soldier, Anglican layman and historian.<ref name="DNZB Norris">{{DNZB|Downs|Jeff|5n13|Hensleigh Carthew Marryat Norris|accessdate=22 December 2016}}</ref>
He had a variety of interests and was awarded life membership by various organisations. Two of his books, ''Armed settlers'' (1956) and ''Settlers in depression'' (1964) are regarded as standard histories for [[Hamilton, New Zealand|Hamilton]] covering the period 1864 to 1894.<ref name="DNZB Norris"/>
He was made a [[Queen's Service Order]] for Community Service (QSO) in the [[1975 Birthday Honours]] for "services to the community".<ref>{{London Gazette|date=6 June 1975|supp=y|issue=46595|page=7406}}</ref>
